<TITLE> Journalist Faiz Ahmed joins CPB </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Feb 6 (bdnews24.com)  Senior journalist Faiz Ahmed joined the Communist Party of Bangladesh on Friday 'to make Bangladesh a socialist state', said a press release on Friday. "I have joined Communist Party of Bangladesh as socialism is the only way to eradicate the all crisis facing the country at the moment," he said. "People cannot get over the crisis without the leftist politics which can be a counterweight to the sort of politics devoid of principles and ideals," Faiz added. He also said he had struggled for life for an oppression-free Bangladesh through the institution of socialism in society. He formally joined the party at the party's national council meeting in the afternoon after the central committee of CPB approved his membership upon his appeal. President Manzurul Ahsan Khan, general secretary Mujahidul Islam Selim and other senior leaders welcomed Faiz. b
